      What is the cost of HP petrol pump?
      Amount of the bid

      15 lakhs for a regular HPCL retail outlet would be charged for dealer-owned or company-leased locations. The minimum bid amount for a Rural HPCL retail outlet is Rs. 10 lakhs, while for normal retail outlets, it is Rs. 30 lakhs.      29 Dec 2023

      What is the real name of petrol pump?
      In Oil Industry parlance, Petrol Pumps are referred to as Retail Outlets (ROs). As per the existing Government policy, Petrol Pumps can be set up by Public Sector Oil Companies as well as Private Sector Oil Companies dealing in storage and distribution of petroleum products as per guidelines.
